The paper deals with improving the performance of intrusion detection classifiers against adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to evaluate the effectiveness of the classifiers, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on network intrusion detection, which falls under the category of network and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also proposes obfuscation techniques to evade detection, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed techniques, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
